Police were called to Mercure Manchester Piccadilly Hotel at around 8.30am following a report of a sex attack.Â A 27-year-old man has been arrested on suspicion of rape and remains in police custody. Photographs shared on Twitter show at least three police cars at the scene, a four-star hotel in the heart of the large city. An ambulance was also seen parked near the entrance to the hotel, Manchester Evening News reports. No further details about the alleged victim, including his age, have been disclosed by police at this stage. But Greater Manchester Police did confirm the arrest was made. A spokesperson for the force said: "Officers were called to a report of a rape just before 8.30am this morning (25 May 2022) at a hotel on Portland Street, Manchester. "Emergency services attended and a male was reported to have been raped by another male. "A 27-year-old man has been arrested on suspicion of rape. He remains in custody at this time. Enquiries are ongoing." 